    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Differentiation</title>
        <table xml:id="auto_3euwh4qv">
            <title>Differentiation Strategies</title>
            <tabular halign="left" bottom="minor" top="minor" left="minor" right="minor">
                <row header="yes" bottom="minor">
                    <cell>Learner Group</cell>
                    <cell>Strategy &amp; Learning Experience</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Struggling Learners</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <line>Provide pre-drawn diagrams with labelled sides (opposite, adjacent, hypotenuse).</line>
                        <line>Use colour-coding: opposite side in red, adjacent side in blue, hypotenuse in green.</line>
                        <line>Start with simple whole-number ratios before moving to decimals.</line>
                        <line>Provide a trigonometric ratios reference card with all three formulas.</line>
                    </cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>On-Level Learners</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <line>Encourage students to explain their reasoning when choosing which ratio to use.</line>
                        <line>Provide mixed practice with different triangle orientations.</line>
                        <line>Ask students to verify their answers using a calculator.</line>
                    </cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Advanced Learners</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <line>Challenge students to find the angle when given the sine or cosine value (inverse functions).</line>
                        <line>Explore the relationship: <m>\tan \theta = \frac{\sin \theta}{\cos \theta}</m>.</line>
                        <line>Investigate complementary angles: <m>\sin \theta = \cos(90^\circ - \theta)</m>.</line>
                        <line>Apply sine and cosine to more complex real-world problems.</line>
                    </cell>
                </row>
            </tabular>
        </table>
        <p xml:id="auto_g0j8ig1o">
            <alert>Extension Activity: Exploring the Relationship Between Sine, Cosine, and Tangent</alert>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_hb9ss8ra">
            Students work in groups to draw right triangles, measure sides and angles, calculate <m>\sin \theta</m>, <m>\cos \theta</m>, and <m>\tan \theta</m>, then divide <m>\sin \theta</m> by <m>\cos \theta</m>. They should discover that <m>\tan \theta = \frac{\sin \theta}{\cos \theta}</m>.
        </p>
    </axiom>

    <xi:include href="../../resources-assessment.ptx" />
